The paper deals with the segment number of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DM). The study of visual complexity of drawings is also related to graph drawing (cs.GR). The use of lower and upper bounds suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on planar graphs and cubic graphs suggests a possible application in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for problems involving spatial reasoning and graph representation.
